    "biography": "<p>The green slime is a horrifying, mindless ooze that clings to ceilings and walls, waiting to drop onto unsuspecting victims.</p><p><strong>Always Hit:</strong> The green slime is AC 20 and can always be hit by attacks.</p><p><strong>Destructive Touch:</strong> It dissolves cloth and leather instantly, wood and metal in 6 rounds, but cannot dissolve stone.</p><p><strong>Body Transformation:</strong> When green slime touches flesh, it sticks and starts transforming the victim into green slime. The process is irreversible after 1d4 rounds unless it is burned off or removed with <em>cure disease</em>.</p><p><strong>Burning & Removal:</strong> Green slime cannot be scraped off. Fire and cold damage it, but fire also harms the victim (splitting damage between both).</p><p><strong>Resistances & Weaknesses:</strong></p><ul><li>Immune to all attacks except fire or cold.</li><li>Cannot be harmed by normal weapons.</li></ul><p><strong>Terrain:</strong> Cavern, Ruins.</p>",
